The continuity touch is very elegantly done, since the mangaka brings in Ooya-chan for a checkup, as well as Sakura-chan. Now, to the specific circumstances in this manga with Ayumi-chan, and how they reflect on the other two heroines in Kokutou's work. None of these three are winning prizes for brilliance. Ayumi was stupid enough to run away from home and end up having to sell her body and her youth to make ends meet. Her boyfriend got her pregnant despite birth control (she implicitly states she was monogamous with him), kicked her out, and she resorted to prostitution (missing tag) to make ends meet. This baby is *NOT* Dr. Yuuma's. She's older than him and pregnant by another man, yet she's the first woman he ends up falling for. Ok, he imprinted on her because she reminds him of his mom. At least she isn’t a man-hunter.

The fact he chose to take responsibility for another man's bastard is something that hits people differently. Many women will admire him, most men will have mixed feelings, since he's wasting his resources on a bastard instead of investing it in his own progeny. Still, he’s a kind, gentle man, so you can’t hate him. However, the second bun in Ayumi’s oven is INDISPUTABLY his. Ayumi emphasizes she doesn’t like sex very much or most men UNTIL she meets Dr. Yuuma. Rather, Dr. Yuuma’s the exception. Her decision to learn how to be a nurse (hard work) in order to support him proves that as well. No one else has been with her and she has no intention of allowing anyone else inside her. She's gone from stupid schoolgirl to desperate prostitute to dedicated wife, when she could have been an amoral golddigger. Why isn't she one?

Ayumi-chan absolutely regrets her life choices to date and attempts to run away to spare Dr. Yuuma from getting wrapped up in her shit. He stops her and acknowledges her past and insists her wants her anyway. Now, how does this reflect on the other two girls, Ooya-chan and Sakura-chan? Ooya-chan is a student who once had good grades, then whored herself to her little brother’s bullies to get them to leave him alone and then fucked her little brother (was he feeling insecure about his sister whoring herself to protect him?), and has an incest bun in the oven. Sakura-chan works for her mother’s restaurant/brothel, and she and her mother are both pregnant from the customers.

There is some implication that Ooya-chan was fond of her sensei before she got into her mess (“one of the reasons I like you, sensei”), and her story suggests she’s interested in more than just money. She doesn’t regret her actions, but she’s more than eager to continue her relationship with her sensei. Sakura-chan’s story hasn’t been translated, but based on the images, she’s also thrilled about having the lover she wants. Both Ooya-chan and Sakura-chan love sex, but they’re also keen to be monogamous. What’s that say about the mangaka? He’s got a pregnancy fetish, that’s obvious. The fact the heroines are all prostitutes suggests his mother might have been one. He probably IS from a single mother home, and wishes he’d had a stable father figure who would have put his buns in his mother’s oven.
